Reasoning: The paper deals with kernelization techniques for several well-studied problems in computer science, including Feedback Arc Set in (Bipartite) Tournaments, Dense Rooted Triplet Inconsistency, and Betweenness in Tournaments. These problems are typically studied in the areas of algorithms, graph theory, and combinatorics, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Based on the content of the paper, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves some game theory concepts, which could place it in the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses techniques from kernelization, which could place it in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
